=====================================

Chat Model in LangChain is a component desined to communicate designed to communicate in a strucuted way with LLMs

https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/integrations/chat

langchain-openai > For connecting with openai

Why do we need langchain Chat models?
To connect to LLMs mainly

1. Consistent workflow:
Langchain chat models unify different APIS saving you from managing each ones unique setup and quirks
2. Easy switching between LLms
Want to switch from one LLM to another ? Langchains chat models make it simple without code rewrites.
3. Context Management
 Working with this help manage conversation history, letting you keep context across multiple interactions seamlessly.
 4. Efficient Chaining
  You can connect multiple LLm calls and task in one structured pipeline, Which is tricky to set up manually.
5. Scallability
 As project grow, Langchain interace supports more complex workflwo, letting you focus on feature not API management.



 CREATE .env file at root


OPENAI_API_KEY= <Api key>

===============

We need to provide access to key using below package

>pip install python-dotenv

=============================

For gemini 
pip install google-genai


=========================================
2. Conversation model

# 1. SystemMessage: Defines the role and sets the context of the conversation
    eg: "You are a marketing expert"
# 2. HumanMessage: Represents users input or questions directed to the AI
    eg: "What's a good marketing stratergy"?
# 3. AIMessage: Contains the AI's responses baon previous messages
    eg: "Focus on social media engagement "

    
